summary: Just found out the amazing Phoebe Waller-Bridge is not only behind the brilliant Fleabag but wrote and developed much of...
body:
Fleabag is comedy as high art

Just found out the amazing Phoebe Waller-Bridge is not only behind the brilliant Fleabag but wrote and developed much of KillingEve.

Fleabag is astonishing and dares to be something new. It’s comedy, tragedy, drama and erotica. It’s had me in hysterics and tears.

Olivia Coleman does a fantastic portrayal of a bitchy stepmother without going over the top in a Disney style. Andrew Scott as a sexy priest is just a bonus.

summary: What gets me is that Villanelle’s assumption is actually correct but she can’t seem to convince herself to indulge in it? I...
caption:
What gets me is that Villanelle’s assumption is actually correct but she can’t seem to convince herself to indulge in it? I wondered if that is why she falls asleep despite being told that she shouldn’t. She enters solitary confinement to find another person in the room and that person feels literally… dead. Villanelle even tells Inga “It’s not worth speaking to you, is it?” because of how non-reactive Inga is to the things Villanelle does or says, an unusal thing for her because her thrill comes from people reacting. That leads to boredom, which is the one thing fatal to Villanelle’s entire being because freedom is her drug.

In that context it also makes sense that Villanelle protects herself from Inga by jumping on her back like a tiger and bites into her neck because it’s not like she couldn’t have killed Inga the entire time? But it’s like watching someone be deprived of their power and then, when you least expect it, they show you what you cannot tame. Villanelle is like that. She doesn’t want to die in there so her instincts kick in. Anyways, I’m speaking outta my ass. Just thought its curious.

summary: I don't think Villanelle is an emotionless sociopath. She cares about a very few select things and people but she does care....
body:
I don’t think Villanelle is an emotionless sociopath. She cares about a very few select things and people but she does care. That’s why Eve and Konstatin were able to manipulate her the way they did. She cares about them in her own way and they appealed to her emotions.

But at the same time, she loves to kill. And she has no qualms about killing as long as it isn’t people she’s personally invested in. (And even then there’s a limit. She was willing to force Konstatin to over-dose on pills and then later shot him in the S1 finale). So I see no redemption in her future. I 100% believe Eve/Villanelle is gonna happen as Eve grows darker, not as Villanelle grows lighter.
